cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with 3D medical imaging techniques and proposes a method to generate new 3D structures using point-cloud representation. This falls under the domain of computer vision and pattern recognition. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed method uses a Gaussian mixture model-based generation scheme, which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a method to generate new samples of medical images, which is an application of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper deals with generating new samples of medical images using a generative model, which can be considered as a neural computing problem. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with 3D shapes represented in terms of point-cloud, which is a graphics-related problem.
